				<h1 class="pagetitle">Three Quarter Layout</h1>
				<div class="box pad grey">
					<h4>The Three Quarter Layout divides content into one 75% width block and one 25% width block.</h4>
					<p>The Three Quarter layout is good for pages that require a small block of content, such as a menu, small instructions section, etc., to be
					floated to the right or left of the main content.</p>
					<p>A single column-three-quarter div can be used to wrap all of the content in a page, keeping
					the content contained in the left three-quarters of a page.  This is useful when it's visually cleaner 
					than stretching that content the width of the screen.</p>
					<p> 
					NOTE: columns only apply to normal to wider screen sizes, since columns scale to 100%
					once the screen size drops to 48em.
					</p>
				</div>
